				posted 2005-03-10 08:05&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=sug&id=2132"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=sug&id=2090"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	    The setting of this game is in the very far future ahead, probably 100,000 years from now. So it might have something which I call a &quot;nuke&quot; is what you call a &quot;nuke&quot; today. A nuke today can cause massive damage to the victim country. And it is only for some serious cases destroy everything in a 10 mile range. So imagine what a &quot;nuke&quot; could do 100,000 years from now? blow up a planet? Come on guys! Haven't you seen/read Star Wars?<br />
    Let me explain. The Empire(in Star Wars) have a weapon called Galaxy Gun. You guys probably never heard this before as it never came out in any of the movies. But i read it in a book.<br />
    This galaxy gun was or will be stationed on The Empire (in Star Wars again) capital planet Byss. This Gun is a space station in orbit and has the ability to fire a missle that can destroy a planet with a single shot. This missle has hyperspace capability and could travel through galaxies in a matter of hours or minutes (depends on the distance of course). The user can also adjust the firepower of this missle from delicate enough to destroy a ship in deep space, a Rebel base on a planet or just simply set to destroy the entire planet.<br />
    This is my original definition of a Superweapon. Of course to obtain this weapon you would have to research almost to the final few technologies in order to build it. And even so it would take a long time and an extremly high cost to develop such a weapon. The difficulty should be that even top players need a few days to develop it.<br />
    This is my concept and hope you people can think about it and maybe Mindwarper could adopt it.			   <P align=right></P>
