			  	Yowza.  Game guys, just a game.  If you read the descriptions of this technology though.....  wow!  I think without actually knowing any of this these guys are doing a great job.  As far as this idea goes....  We have a &quot;super weapon&quot; guys.....  Homing Black Hole.  I think it's kinda funny that somebody was worried about creating a black hole by destroying a planet, because here we are flinging temporary black holes all over the place.  For the purposes of the game, however, this is one case where realism needs to be sacrificed somewhat for gameplay.  Assuming we have massive, planet sized ships doing battle near the atmosphere of a planet.....  What is to keep one or two of those doomstars from wandering over to that planet, hurling a couple rounds of HBH's and flying away?  If destroying a planet were this easy there would be some serious issues with gameplay.  Scarey to think that this could be our future :)			   <P align=right></P>
